In the face of the backlash, Starbucks announced over the weekend that baristas will no longer be encouraged to write 'Race Together' on customers' cups.

The initiative ended on Sunday, but spokesperson Jim Olson denied that the phase out was a reaction to the push back the chain has received.

'Nothing is changing,' he said. 'It's all part of the cadence of the timeline we originally planned.'

